# {{.Name}}

A product built on the [wowapi](https://github.com/qatoolist/wowapi/v2) framework.

## Getting started

The runtime is fail-closed: `environment` and the DB DSNs must be set explicitly —
there is no silent default. Select the config overlay with `APP_ENV` and provide the
DSN secrets the `secretref://env/…` values in `configs/local.yaml` point at:

```bash
# 1. Select the local overlay (configs/local.yaml) for every command below.
export APP_ENV=local

# 2. Provide the DSN secrets. app_rt is the non-privileged runtime login; app_platform
#    is a dedicated cross-tenant login (api/worker fail closed without it); app_migrate
#    owns the schema. For local dev these may all point at the same superuser DB.
export DATABASE_URL="postgres://app_rt:secret@localhost:5432/{{.DBName}}?sslmode=disable"
export PLATFORM_URL="postgres://app_platform:secret@localhost:5432/{{.DBName}}?sslmode=disable"
export MIGRATE_URL="postgres://app_migrate:secret@localhost:5432/{{.DBName}}?sslmode=disable"

# 3. Validate config, run migrations, then the API server.
wowapi config validate --dir configs --env local
go run ./cmd/migrate up
go run ./cmd/api
```

## Structure

```
cmd/
  api/        HTTP API server entry point
  worker/     Background worker entry point
  migrate/    Migration runner entry point
configs/
  base.yaml   Base configuration (committed)
  local.yaml  Local developer overlay (gitignored)
internal/
  modules/    Product modules (wowapi module.Module implementations)
```
